    "answered_user_question": "Yes, MORI can be fixed for the MBS4 no-AC memory failure on MI350. The failure was not because 287 GiB is intrinsically too small; it came from several giant padded temporary allocations plus allocator fragmentation/heap pressure. The compact/streamed path survives with 243.84-246.03 GiB peak logged memory.",
    "remaining_wall": "After the memory fix, the main MORI/MoE wall is not dTopk combine or dispatch. It is owner-rank local VJP math plus dX return wait. In step 4, the slowest rank spends 7.513s in local VJP while another spends 4.749s in combine_dx waiting/returning, making the rank totals align around 9.27s.",
    "next_optimization_target": "Replace or fuse the padded owner-rank VJP math. The largest late-step inner stages are W13 forward recompute, W2 dgrad/wgrad, W2 forward recompute, and W13/SwiGLU backward. The streamed path fixed memory but remains a PyTorch/GEMM-family training VJP, so the next materializable speed path is an AITER/CK training backward that exposes/saves usable forward intermediates without slowing AITER fused forward, or a fused owner VJP that avoids repeated padded forward recompute."
